<subSubSection id="E0B648579327100AA8FA9DED9F82EC91" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="16E5B315AEBA9D00955B98D822D96ED3" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="51C80014255098EFABB60DA090BF951A" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<taxonomicName id="42A6B158D0AAE41F91EF6AA5A0E6FE58" class="Anthozoa" family="Nephtheidae" genus="Litophyton" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Litophyton" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">Litophyton</taxonomicName>
with the internal spindles of the base of the stalk mostly with pointed ends. Polyp stalk with scales, surface of the stalk with straight spindles and unilaterally spinose spindles.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A6E76CCBFC1766A43780BE9D3B8583C5" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="B11B44B12A755DB388B2B1E890303EA6" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="66C9AED15FAC4175E8B834B136A8F022" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Only known from the type locality Madagascar.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E70F6078D2C11D4DB74AD298D4D20CB5" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="A56781311549934530177A0ABE55B356" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="688D72365B055E19352C29780CC96F64" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
The species is sufficiently described by 
<bibRefCitation id="1C9897AA22E4AD45ACEE92D061C99119" author="Verseveldt, J" journalOrPublisher="Amsterdam" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="69 - 171" title="Octocorallia from north-western Madagascar (Part IIIa-d)." volumeTitle="Proceedings Koninklijke Nederlandse Akademie van Wetenschappen" year="1973">Verseveldt (1973</bibRefCitation>
: 141). Here I present the holotype colony shape (Figure 33) and SEM images of its sclerites (Figures 34-35).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="89241C906268E418A4C6CE3693EAC57E" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
The species mostly resembles 
<taxonomicName id="3CB1EA89946C84D0A9677507C799D6E6" class="Anthozoa" family="Nephtheidae" genus="Litophyton" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Litophyton curvum" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="curvum">Litophyton curvum</taxonomicName>
but differs in having straight sclerites in the surface layer of the base of the stalk and very spiny, almost spheroidal, sclerites in the surface layer of the base of the stalk.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FBCC96B46FED65E73870E06DA2921422" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
RMNH Coel. 12966 and RMNH Coel. 14596 are misidentifications. The specimens have no rodlets on the adaxial side of the polyp, as is the case in 
<taxonomicName id="46F373BF3B1DE81BC31CFEEEB12C6C0B" class="Anthozoa" family="Nephtheidae" genus="Litophyton" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Litophyton filamentosum" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="filamentosum">Litophyton filamentosum</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
